{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"29c0f5e1-7ad7-4e4a-8080-3c880e5b67cb","content":"There's no workflow file in the current directory, so here's the general guidance for switching to NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC):\n\n### 1. Configure your NuGet.org package\n\nOn **nuget.org → Manage Packages → your package → Trusted Publishers**, add a GitHub Actions publisher:\n- **Repository owner/name** — e.g. `myorg/myrepo`\n- **Workflow file** — e.g. `publish.yml`\n- Optionally restrict to a specific **branch/tag/environment**\n\n### 2. Update your GitHub Actions workflow\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    # ── NEW: request an OIDC token ──\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write   # required for OIDC\n      contents: read\n\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      - uses: actions/setup-dotnet@v4\n        with:\n          dotnet-version: '8.x'\n\n      - run: dotnet pack -c Release\n\n      # ── REPLACE the old push step ──\n      # OLD:\n      #   dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg \\\n      #     --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }} \\\n      #     --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n      #\n      # NEW:\n      - run: >\n          dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg\n          --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n### Key changes\n\n| Before | After |\n|---|---|\n| `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` passed via `--api-key` | No API key needed — remove it |\n| No `permissions` block | Add `id-token: write` |\n| Any runner | Same runner (no other change) |\n\nThe `dotnet nuget push` command automatically discovers the OIDC token when `id-token: write` is set and the NuGet.org trusted-publisher config matches the calling workflow.\n\n### 3. Clean up\n\n- Delete the `NUGET_API_KEY` secret from your repo/org settings once you've verified the new flow works.\n\nWould you like me to create or edit a specific workflow file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"494b87d4-a4a3-49c7-b55f-317a539802ea","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty - there's no repository to look at. The user is asking a general question about switching from NuGet API key-based publishing to NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC) in GitHub Actions. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":612,"requestId":"4C0C:8D0D7:60B3756:6BE5F6D:69EC0EEB"},"id":"1462d06d-f46e-4d9c-943f-9557058da674","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:46:49.566Z","parentId":"3354447a-2e45-49f1-bfb9-4b0f14293c01"}
